+# Tenant Web Pages Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Replace 15 Placeholder routes with real tenant and shared web pages, desktop-first power-user oriented.
+
+**Architecture:** Each page is a standalone React component in `web/src/pages/tenant/` or `web/src/pages/shared/`, using existing services, shared components (`EmptyState`, `ErrorState`, `StatCard`), and the `TenantLayout`/`LandlordLayout` shells. Follows the same patterns as the landlord batch: local `useState` + `useCallback` + `useEffect`, loading skeletons, error/empty states, lucide-react icons.
+
+**Tech Stack:** React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, react-router-dom v7, lucide-react, existing service layer
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- All pages use the existing `web/src/services/` layer — no new API calls
+- Every page handles: loading (skeleton), error (ErrorState), empty (EmptyState), and data states
+- Catch blocks use type assertion: `(err as any)?.response?.data?.message ?? (err as any)?.message ?? 'fallback'`
+- No form validation library — plain inline checks matching existing patterns
+- Icons from `lucide-react` only
+- Color tokens: `brand-green`, `emerald`, `amber`, `muted`, `destructive`, `primary`, `foreground`, `muted-foreground`
+- All pages use `formatNGN`, `formatDate`, `timeAgo` from `@/lib/utils`
+
